1
00:00:13,488 --> 00:00:15,350
Are you the one
we're looking for? Come here.

2
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:19,000
Found you.

3
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,670
Looks like
that snuff bottle is mine now.

4
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:24,440
Look.

5
00:00:28,160 --> 00:00:29,030
Is this blood?

6
00:00:31,860 --> 00:00:35,580
=Cases Between Us=

7
00:00:36,020 --> 00:00:38,340
=Episode 20=

8
00:00:38,350 --> 00:00:39,110
Why are you here?

9
00:00:39,110 --> 00:00:40,110
Where's your daughter?

10
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,070
She's bleeding heavily.

11
00:01:18,070 --> 00:01:19,350
She needs a doctor.

12
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,510
Du's out of town.

13
00:01:20,790 --> 00:01:21,760
Get one of his students.

14
00:01:43,150 --> 00:01:44,230
How is she, doctor?

15
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,200
I've stitched the wound.

16
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,200
She should be fine.

17
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:49,230
Don't worry.

18
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,480
Thank you.

19
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,070
Director Li.

20
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:52,950
Who handles

21
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:54,070
the meals

22
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:54,950
in your house?

23
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,870
The cooking?

24
00:01:57,510 --> 00:01:58,510
Ms. Zhang.

25
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:00,430
She's our housekeeper.

26
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,150
Why?

27
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:02,480
I suspect

28
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:04,790
someone drugged your daughter.

29
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:08,280
I found this

30
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,030
in the trash.

31
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,590
Opium tincture.

32
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,000
What?

33
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,120
Opium tincture.

34
00:02:32,288 --> 00:02:34,064
It stimulates
the central nervous system.

35
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:35,710
It can cause extreme excitement,

36
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:36,896
hallucinations, and delusions.

37
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:37,800
In severe cases,

38
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,280
it can be life-threatening.

39
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:04,910
Chief Yuan,

40
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:06,430
here's a photo of Ms. Zhang.

41
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,190
Please.

42
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:09,870
Find her.

43
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:11,710
Dead or alive.

44
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:16,310
Someone must've bribed her.

45
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,030
And whoever did it knows medicine.

46
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:20,470
Opium tincture

47
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,120
is only available

48
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,310
in hospitals or the military.

49
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,430
I'm afraid

50
00:03:25,648 --> 00:03:27,590
your daughter
may have crossed someone powerful.

51
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:38,280
Maomao.

52
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:40,000
Maomao.

53
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,310
My daughter keeps to herself.

54
00:03:47,664 --> 00:03:49,744
She coops herself up,
either reading in the study

55
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,280
or talking to her dog.

56
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,560
She found the dog last night.

57
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,150
But when she got home,
her hair was a mess,

58
00:03:57,630 --> 00:03:59,030
and she'd lost a shoe.

59
00:03:59,190 --> 00:03:59,800
Mom!

60
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:01,680
Mom!

61
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:05,560
I saw a mummy!

62
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,630
Bandages.

63
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,992
Its face was wrapped in bandages.

64
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:10,280
I really did!

65
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,240
Mummy?

66
00:04:13,584 --> 00:04:14,560
Neither Ms. Zhang nor I

67
00:04:14,592 --> 00:04:16,208
could make sense of what she was saying.

68
00:04:16,352 --> 00:04:17,360
She couldn't explain it,

69
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:18,830
so she started drawing.

70
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:28,360
This is it.

71
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,240
Uh.

72
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,360
What is this?

73
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:40,950
That's it.

74
00:04:40,950 --> 00:04:41,720
Mummy.

75
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:42,720
A corpse.

76
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,310
Aren't those from overseas?

77
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,680
A corpse?

78
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,120
It's dead.

79
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:50,480
Siqiao,

80
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:51,430
maybe you were frightened

81
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,430
and imagined it.

82
00:04:52,430 --> 00:04:54,270
I wasn't imagining things! I saw it!

83
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,480
Madam,

84
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,920
Young Lady must've been frightened.

85
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,950
Drink your milk.

86
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,160
I'm not drinking that!

87
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,630
You're saying

88
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,070
she keeps saying those things

89
00:05:27,136 --> 00:05:28,830
because the drug
is making her hallucinate?

90
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:29,310
right?

91
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:35,390
Before the hallucinations begin,

92
00:05:35,504 --> 00:05:37,680
there'll be a period
of agitation and excessive talking.

93
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:39,750
Do you remember

94
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:40,750
when she first started

95
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:41,830
acting strangely?

96
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:46,240
She didn't say much last night.

97
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,630
It was around noon today

98
00:05:47,664 --> 00:05:49,070
that she suddenly became agitated.

99
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,120
She kept talking about that mummy.

100
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,270
She kept saying

101
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:53,920
a monster was going to kill Maomao

102
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,430
and cut him open.

103
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,920
After lunch?

104
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,870
Why didn't you

105
00:05:57,870 --> 00:05:59,310
call me?

106
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,600
Haven't you been busy
working on the transfer...

107
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,000
Transfer?

108
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,070
Nothing.

109
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,830
Director Li,

110
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,800
if you're holding something back,

111
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,720
we may not be able to help you.

112
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:36,040
There is no time to keep secrets.

113
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:37,120
Tell them.

114
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,830
I've been working on
a transfer to Customs.

115
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,510
Could it be

116
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,510
that someone's trying to stop you?

117
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,800
Why did they drug Siqiao?

118
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,190
Drug?

119
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:04,680
Exactly.

120
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,240
Why did they drug Siqiao?

121
00:07:14,190 --> 00:07:15,630
May we borrow your dog?

122
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,750
About half an hour
southwest of the Li Residence,

123
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:25,430
it should be around here.

124
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,070
This must be where she saw the mummy.

125
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,000
You're up.

126
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,070
This is it.

127
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,310
Come here.

128
00:07:48,688 --> 00:07:50,120
The direction the dog's afraid of

129
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,720
is probably where we're headed.

130
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,190
You sure think like a dog.

131
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,510
Animal psychology.

132
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,190
This is the place.

133
00:08:06,860 --> 00:08:08,700
(Renshou Alley,
Inner Right District Two)

134
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:37,670
This must be the house

135
00:08:37,670 --> 00:08:40,030
the Sanlihe Police Station
said was on fire, right?

136
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:41,150
That's right.

137
00:08:41,790 --> 00:08:42,510
It was rented by

138
00:08:42,510 --> 00:08:44,224
a British missionary, Pans.

139
00:08:44,272 --> 00:08:45,790
(Pans, Beijing Foreign Entry Register)
He'd been preaching around the country.

140
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,150
Staying in Beijing for six months,

141
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,790
(Dong Zhi)
he adopted two Chinese orphans.

142
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:49,750
(Lin Wen)
A boy and a girl.

143
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,910
(Adopted Dong Zhi and Wen six months ago)
The dead one is the boy.

144
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,000
He adopted two children
and rented a place this big?

145
00:08:54,064 --> 00:08:55,480
Does missionary work pay that well?

146
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:58,600
I'll check over there.

147
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,150
Kerosene.

148
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:04,080
Zhao Shaoshang.

149
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:04,870
Over here.

150
00:10:18,304 --> 00:10:19,568
The dog's afraid of this place.

151
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,720
This must be it.

152
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,080
You're starting to think like a dog now.

153
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,390
Stay here.

154
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:33,960
I'll come back for you later.

155
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,320
Wait for me.

156
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:38,910
Let's go.

157
00:11:04,064 --> 00:11:05,952
Looks like someone
cleaned this place up.

158
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:12,150
Smell this.

159
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,030
Is that dog poop?

160
00:11:14,624 --> 00:11:16,240
You already knew. Why make me smell it?

161
00:11:16,790 --> 00:11:18,840
If you don't smell it,
how am I supposed to know?

162
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,630
Maomao was probably locked up here.

163
00:11:26,864 --> 00:11:28,670
Maomao wasn't
the only one locked up here.

164
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:30,960
There were others?

165
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,390
Judging by the paw prints,
at least three or four.

166
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,440
Does the priest eat dogs?

167
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,150
Help!

168
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:41,360
Thief!

169
00:11:41,670 --> 00:11:43,030
Help!

170
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,440
Thief!

171
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:46,360
Don't hit me.

172
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,510
You're hitting cops.

173
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:49,790
You're laughing?

174
00:11:49,856 --> 00:11:51,600
You started beating
without seeing?

175
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,910
Didn't you see his uniform?

176
00:11:53,024 --> 00:11:54,150
Look what you've done to me.

177
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:55,200
My hair's ruined.

178
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:55,720
Well,

179
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:56,030
you two

180
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:57,960
just barged in without saying a word.

181
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,030
Of course, I thought

182
00:11:59,030 --> 00:12:00,550
you were thieves.

183
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:01,200
Exactly.

184
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,390
It was pitch black in there,

185
00:12:02,390 --> 00:12:03,670
and everyone started fighting.

186
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:04,790
How was I supposed to tell?

187
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:06,600
Go on and talk.

188
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,080
Come.

189
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:08,750
No, no.

190
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:11,536
You know the priest pretty well.

191
00:12:11,552 --> 00:12:12,790
Are you looking after his home?

192
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:13,630
Of course.

193
00:12:13,910 --> 00:12:15,030
He speaks great Chinese

194
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:16,440
and is kind.

195
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,550
He never puts on airs,

196
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:18,800
unlike the other foreigners.

197
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:21,480
How was he with the two children?

198
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,120
You have no idea

199
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,790
how much Father Pans doted

200
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,320
on Dong Zhi.

201
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,750
Like he was his own son.

202
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,750
Dong Zhi was weak.

203
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,870
Father Pans

204
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:33,720
had his family send money from overseas

205
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,270
to buy him meat and milk.

206
00:12:35,270 --> 00:12:36,256
Everything went to him.

207
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:37,720
Wen, the older sister,

208
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,960
had been jealous.

209
00:12:40,510 --> 00:12:41,360
Good thing

210
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,270
she couldn't speak.

211
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:43,600
Otherwise,

212
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,550
who knows how much
she would've cursed him?

213
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,480
She can't speak?

214
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,440
She's mute?

215
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,080
That's right.

216
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:52,270
Don't let her fool you. She can't speak,
but she's got a mean streak.

217
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,240
One time,

218
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,320
I saw Dong Zhi

219
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,510
bring home a stray dog.

220
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:57,000
She kicked it away.

221
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,910
Was it this one?

222
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:00,848
Doesn't look like it.

223
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:01,670
Oh, right.

224
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:02,910
About 1 km south of here,

225
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,120
there's a dump.

226
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,550
It's crawling

227
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:07,440
with stray dogs.

228
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,670
This isn't a stray.

229
00:13:09,136 --> 00:13:10,640
- No, it isn't.
- No, it isn't.

230
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,888
Have either of the children

231
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:13,056
been injured recently?

232
00:13:13,670 --> 00:13:14,750
Injured?

233
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,080
With bandages on their face?

234
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:18,870
No.

235
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:20,910
Did either of you see anything?

236
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,750
Can't say for sure.

237
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,776
I didn't see either of them
for several days

238
00:13:25,792 --> 00:13:27,030
before the fire.

239
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,150
I did see the girl, though.

240
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:31,390
The afternoon before yesterday.

241
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,200
I ran into her.

242
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:35,630
She came running out of the house.

243
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,030
These vegetables are so fresh.

244
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:38,910
Hey.

245
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:41,480
Watch where you're going.

246
00:13:41,744 --> 00:13:43,120
You nearly knocked me over.

247
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:43,960
Jeez.

248
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,750
Running around like that.

249
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,030
Right after she ran out,

250
00:13:49,030 --> 00:13:50,320
the house caught fire.

251
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:53,000
Could it be her who started it?

252
00:13:54,464 --> 00:13:56,120
Don't jump to conclusions
without evidence.

253
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:58,200
- Alright, alright.
- Yes.

254
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,390
Tell me,

255
00:13:59,390 --> 00:14:00,750
are those two blood siblings?

256
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,480
Well,

257
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:04,440
I don't think so.

258
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,990
If a girl barely in her teens
set the fire out of jealousy

259
00:14:12,030 --> 00:14:13,790
and burned her adopted brother alive,

260
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,000
that's possible.

261
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:17,480
But getting hold of opium tincture

262
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,390
to silence a witness,

263
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:19,480
no way.

264
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,150
Father Pans.

265
00:14:24,540 --> 00:14:26,080
(Pans)

266
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:26,910
Who are you?

267
00:14:27,056 --> 00:14:29,480
Yuan Hong, Division Four Chief,
Jingshi Police Department.

268
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,480
Zhao Shaoshang,
Investigative Consultant.

269
00:14:31,584 --> 00:14:32,630
We're here to follow up

270
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:33,750
on the fire two days ago.

271
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:44,000
You've been to my house?

272
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:48,910
Did you find anything?

273
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:51,270
Same as the police report.

274
00:14:51,270 --> 00:14:52,120
Nothing unusual.

275
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,200
But

276
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,390
where's Wen?

277
00:14:55,870 --> 00:14:57,080
I've been looking for her, too.

278
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,440
I haven't seen her

279
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,510
since the fire.

280
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:06,630
Where have you just come from?

281
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:08,790
The cemetery on the outskirts.

282
00:15:08,790 --> 00:15:10,240
I went to see my child off

283
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,200
one last time.

284
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,200
Dong Zhi's already been buried?

285
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:16,440
Where?

286
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,536
You've confirmed there was
nothing suspicious about the fire.

287
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,510
Please don't disturb the dead.

288
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:27,670
Please excuse me.

289
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:30,510
I have to meet the landlord now

290
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:31,720
to discuss compensation.

291
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,360
One moment, Father Pans.

292
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,270
Do you know Zhang Hualan?

293
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:37,790
Who?

294
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:38,970
A maid.

295
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:40,790
She often shopped at the market

296
00:15:40,790 --> 00:15:42,270
next to your church.

297
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:47,790
She looks familiar,

298
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:49,840
but I don't know her.

299
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,390
Sorry.

300
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,910
I'm a priest.

301
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,960
I meet too many people every day.

302
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:57,630
Where are you staying now?

303
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,600
If you won't tell us,

304
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,510
I'll have someone keep an eye on you.

305
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:15,600
International Hotel. Room 901.

306
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:30,960
There's something off about the priest.

307
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,720
You think so too?

308
00:16:36,550 --> 00:16:37,550
The dog does.

309
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:39,960
It takes one to know one.

310
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,480
Anyway, there was something odd
about his leg.

311
00:16:42,670 --> 00:16:44,960
When he arrived, he was limping badly.

312
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:47,376
He was avoiding putting weight
on his left leg.

313
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:48,360
But when he left,

314
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,360
his gait was normal.

315
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,600
If he were really injured,

316
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,080
how could he recover
in just a few minutes?

317
00:16:54,624 --> 00:16:56,544
He's trying too hard
to cover something up.

318
00:16:56,592 --> 00:16:57,790
What do you think he's hiding?

319
00:16:59,270 --> 00:16:59,790
Answer me.

320
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,320
Say something.

321
00:17:07,110 --> 00:17:08,160
Maomao's good dog.

322
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:09,160
So well-behaved.

323
00:17:29,070 --> 00:17:30,350
You trust me, do you?

324
00:17:31,830 --> 00:17:34,110
Do you trust me?

325
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:39,550
That mummy

326
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:41,310
cut Maomao's vocal cords.

327
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,070
He can't bark anymore.

328
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,270
Director Li's dog

329
00:17:53,270 --> 00:17:54,270
had its vocal cords cut.

330
00:17:54,288 --> 00:17:56,976
I stopped by the dog meat shop and
found three dogs that couldn't bark.

331
00:17:57,030 --> 00:17:58,576
Give them all a thorough examination.

332
00:17:59,790 --> 00:18:01,240
You had me work as a medical examiner,

333
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,350
and I put up with that.

334
00:18:02,448 --> 00:18:03,830
Now you want me to be a vet, too?

335
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:04,790
What?

336
00:18:04,790 --> 00:18:06,510
Am I going
to perform exorcisms next time?

337
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:08,070
Two silver coins per dog.

338
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,590
It's not about the money.

339
00:18:11,920 --> 00:18:12,440
Sit.

340
00:18:13,310 --> 00:18:14,400
I'll handle that.

341
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:18,240
Hey,

342
00:18:18,550 --> 00:18:19,312
give me a hand.

343
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,000
Put them there.

344
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,400
Let me check.

345
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,270
Chief Yuan,

346
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:45,590
come here.

347
00:18:46,480 --> 00:18:47,568
Every one of these dogs

348
00:18:47,584 --> 00:18:49,310
has needle marks
and signs of being tied up.

349
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:59,880
Chief, Father Pans bought a train ticket
from Beijing to Shanghai.

350
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:00,830
He leaves tonight.

351
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:01,920
Let's go.

352
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,000
Wait.

353
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:03,720
My money.

354
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:04,880
Get it from Zhao Shaoshang.

355
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,200
Good dog.

356
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:12,700
(End of Episode 20)

357
00:19:14,321 --> 00:19:15,961
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

358
00:19:15,961 --> 00:19:17,501
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

359
00:19:17,501 --> 00:19:18,751
♪However, the world changes♪

360
00:19:18,751 --> 00:19:20,671
♪You'll still be by my side♪

361
00:19:20,671 --> 00:19:22,361
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

362
00:19:22,361 --> 00:19:23,931
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

363
00:19:23,931 --> 00:19:25,501
♪If this is my final chapter♪

364
00:19:25,501 --> 00:19:28,001
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
